data.text:
2023 (Jr.) | 10/1: Borland appeared in 10 games, with one start against Sam Houston, during his first season with WKU and provided depth at the tight end position. He caught one pass on the year – also in the 28-23 win over Sam Houston on Nov. 18 – for 4 yards.

Before WKU: Borland played four seasons at Buffalo, primarily as a blocking tight end. He also caught 18 passes for 146 yards and a touchdown for the Bulls during his time there.

HS/Misc.: Borland was a three-time letterwinner at Bolingbrook High School while also serving as a team captain. He was a two-time all-conference selection.
